  "body": "Hi guys!\r\n\r\nI am maintaining an archive Dockerised Optimism node, and my service needs to poll it with `debug_traceTransaction` calls.\r\nWhen I try to poll the node, it gets out of sync and remains about 300 blocks behind the tip. Moreover, about 3 out of 10 calls themselves are timed out.\r\nI know that this call is quite heavy. \r\nWill Bedrock fix this? Is there any workaround so far?\r\n\r\nThank you in advance!",
